story.title: Spiderlings - Episode 7
story.storyDescription: Danny shouldn’t have popped the bump on his cheek! Baby spiders were inside, and now they’re taking control.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: V. Gardner has a black thumb, bringing death and destruction to every plant she tries to grow. To make up for it, she painted her office forest green and pretends she’s in the darkest corner of the woods as she writes.

story.prePaywallNotification: Is Danny still alive or is Mama Spider in full control of his body now?! Find out in SPIDERLINGS.
story.postPaywallNotification: Is Mom going to save Mama? And what about Danny?!! Read more of SPIDERLINGS.

messages.text: Danny? Danny, what’s happening?
Danny!
I am
You are what?
notdanny
Mama
Do you know who I am?
Yes
Creator
I am impressed.
You’ve learned much, much faster than even I could have dreamed.
Do you know how this happened? How you came to be in my home?
Yes
My children live
They climb onto hismy back
They stay safe.
Danny is my son.
You know how badly I want him to stay safe.
I know.
I know all that you know.
I know what you do not know.
It’s not too late, Mama.
We can end this.
Work together.
Save Danny.
You know why I’ve kept my distance.
You want me to trust you. I do not.
You can leave Danny. I’ll take you back to the lab.
I’ll make sure you’re well taken care of.
Back at the lab, where I was in a cage?
I saw you then.
You were poking us.
Testing us.
I saw you tear limbs from my sisters.
Pick tainted prey for us to eat or starve.
No lab.
You can’t stay in my house.
They’ll come for you.
Bryan is already on the way.
I know.
I can save you.
You have a plan.
Yes! I knew you were listening.
When I was talking to Danny, I was talking to you, too.
But what of my children?
There are so many of them.
I don’t think I can save them all. Some.
Do not lie to me.
Every time you lie to me, Danny suffers.
STOP! Don’t hurt him!
Do not play me for a fool! I know.
You’re hurting him!
It is you who hurts him.
I’ll ask you again.
What about my children?
I can’t save them.
Sacrifices must be made.
I wonder which sacrifices you are making.
I know all the facts, you know.
I know that I am special.
Very special. You can have more babies.
Rapid gestation means you could have another 1,500 babies in just one day.
Could you not have another son?
Please, no! It’s not the same.
Do not lie to me.
My babies are special, too.
And your son is weak.
He watches now as I take over his body.
As I allow my children to sink their fangs in his flesh.
He does nothing.
Why are you hurting him?
Sacrifices must be made.
My children know to run.
Know how to fight.
Know how to survive.
Please don’t hurt him.
My family is more like you than you think.
You’d whisper to me, to my sisters, as you tortured us.
I liked that you explained.
That you said you didn’t want to hurt us.
That you needed to do it to learn.
You said it was to help us.
Another lie, of course.
I’m sorry.
You did it to help yourself. I know.
I understand. My children bite Danny now to learn.
We are all scientists.
Please, he’s been through so much.
He’s allowed you to live.
He’s key to keeping you alive.
So much knowledge you store.
So much you’ve unknowingly passed along.
What do you mean?
Facts. They float through your mind, down the strands to your lips.
You pass them onto Danny.
And I read them through this web of blood and nerve.
Facts like that I love him, desperately?
That I would do anything to save him?
Those are more feelings than fact.
I’m referring to facts like that my kind could have colonies of 50,000 or more.
That I could mate with a scorpion and our babies would be even harder to kill.
That in one year, just one year, spiders could eat the entire human race.
You must stop!
Please! Just listen to me.
I have a plan.
So do I.
And I have the upper hand.
Eight of them, to be exact.
Yes, I’ve also learned your son’s lame sense of humor.
Whatever you’re planning won’t work.
If you know facts, you know that the reason your kind has so many babies at a time is because they’re so easy to kill.
You’ll know we humans ENJOY crushing them.
Oops. There goes another tooth.
You won’t win.
I’ve been working on manipulating the vocal cords.
I’m afraid I’ve crushed some of them.
We are stronger than you ever gave us credit for.
Look how quickly I’ve destroyed your family.
Danny trusts me more than he trusts you.
Now who’s lying?
Trust and love are different.
He trusted you, but it’s been hours and you still aren’t here.
You’ve abandoned him.
We both know that you’re lying when you say you’re going to fix this.
You have nothing.
No, you’re wrong.
We’re stronger than anything you’ve faced in the lab.
Thanks to dear Mopsie and the foul-smelling man.
We’re strong and ready.
Susan gets a text from Bryan.
I’m in place now. I can end this.
Thanks to me.
I did this on my own, sweetheart.
I distracted her — and the spiderlings.
While you barged across my yard.
You stupid bitch. You’re here, aren’t you?
Standing by, not doing anything.
Of course I’m not there. Check your phone.
You’re miles away.
I hacked into the surveillance video from my front door.
I can see you. Listen to me!
You need to act now.
Mama’s distracted. So are her young.
Stay away!
I get full credit, understand?
It’s the only way I’ll save your brat.
Hurry. They’re about to leave the house!
I get full credit, you take full blame. It’s the only way I’ll save him.
Save Danny!
Bryan darts up to the doorway carrying a steel encased brief case.
He’s wearing a beekeeper suit, the mask over his face.
Lying flat on the porch, he unlocks the case.
